meanings.definition: The act or process of expanding beyond normal limits.
meanings.sent1: The overexpansions of the balloon made it burst.
meanings.sent2: The city's overexpansions led to traffic congestion.
meanings.sent3: The overexpansions of the cake batter caused a messy kitchen.
meanings.sent4: Her overexpansions of the truth made it hard to trust her.
meanings.sent5: The overexpansions of the tree roots cracked the sidewalk.

meanings.definition: The state of being expanded beyond normal limits.
meanings.sent1: The overexpansions of the budget caused financial issues.
meanings.sent2: The overexpansions of the population strained public services.
meanings.sent3: The overexpansions of the suitcase made it impossible to close.
meanings.sent4: His overexpansions of his abilities led to disappointment.
meanings.sent5: The overexpansions of the river flooded the nearby fields.
